cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SI 

The paper deals with text analytics and machine learning classifiers applied to a seismological corpus, which suggests a strong connection to the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of various standard models such as Naive Bayes, k-Nearest Neighbors, Support Vector Machines, and Random Forests, as well as the investigation of classification processes, points to a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the study of earthquake predictability research and the analysis of trends in this field suggest a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
